reports.description: Dynamic analysis on Microsoft Windows XP

malicious_activity: Autostart: Registering a scheduled task
Autostart: Registering for autostart during Windows boot
Evasion: Disables Windows Error Reporting for a process
Evasion: Possibly stalling against analysis environment (sleep)
Evasion: Trying to detect analysis virtual environment (PnP device detection)
Execution: Ability to iterate through running processes
Execution: Ability to load DLL by remote process (code injection)
Execution: Ability to use cryptography API
File: Modifying executable in user-shared data directory
Memory: Replacing the image of a process with the same original executable (potential unpacking)
Memory: Replacing the image of another process (detection evasion or privilege escalation)
Memory: Writing to the memory of a non-child running process
Network: Ability to download files from the Internet
Network: Attempting to download executable from remote location
Network: Connecting to server using hard-coded IP address
Network: Failing to communicate with server
Network: Hide network activity through code injection
Network: Repeated DNS lookup failure (potential DGA)
Packer: Loading an embedded PE image (potential unpacking)
Search: Enumerates running processes
Search: Retrieving the user account name
Signature: Identified trojan code
Steal: Reading system license information
